  Apps), wrong paths (src/... vs app/backend/src/...), and contradictory
  logging guidance (structured logging only vs console.log()).

  One false positive: the 90-day freshness warning can flag accurate,
  intentionally stable docs.

  One hard negative: the scripts won’t reliably catch semantically
  wrong-but-existing guidance, like outdated technology choices or
  contradictory behavior rules.

  Maintenance cadence: weekly quick audit, monthly stale-reference/dedup
  review, quarterly deep review, plus event-driven checks after refactors,
  dependency/platform changes, or doc moves.

  Prioritized fixes:

   1. Fix stale technology/path references.
   2. Remove contradictions.
   3. Split over-specified global rules into scoped .instructions.md.
   4. Deduplicate copy-pasted guidance.
   5. Tighten under-specified rules with short actionable constraints.


